-- ABB, Actelion, Swatch, UBS Shares: Swiss Equity Preview
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-09-30T06:42:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-30/abb-actelion-swatch-ubs-shares-may-move-in-zurich-swiss-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of
companies whose shares may have unusual price changes in Zurich.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names. Share
prices are from the last close.  The  Swiss Market Index  of the biggest and most actively
traded companies fell 0.4 percent to 6,311.57 in Zurich. The
broader  Swiss Performance Index  declined 0.3 percent.  ABB Ltd.  (ABBN VX): Two units of the world’s biggest
electricity-networks builder were charged by the U.S. with
conspiracy and violating the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act. The
company has agreed to pay about $58.3 million to resolve claims
by U.S. prosecutors and regulators that its units made corrupt
payments to win business in Mexico and Iraq. The shares rose 0.3
percent to 20.8 Swiss francs.  Actelion Ltd.  (ATLN VX): Credit Suisse Group AG downgraded
Switzerland’s largest biotechnology company was cut to
“neutral” from “outperform.” The shares rose 0.1 percent to
39.95 Swiss francs.  Swatch Group AG  (UHR VX): Sanford Bernstein raised its
recommendation for the watchmaker to “outperform.” The shares
rose 0.6 percent to 362.9 francs.  UBS AG  (UBSN VX): Switzerland’s biggest bank said it
probably won’t pay dividends for “some time” to satisfy new
capital requirements without selling shares. The bank also said
its risk-weighted assets would rise under Basel III standards,
according to presentation slides by the company’s Chief
Financial Officer John Cryan. The shares dropped 2.4 percent to
17.06 francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah Jones in London at 
